We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive adopt/design measures to improve the collection of monthly electric bill payments from the stallholders in order to avoid instances whereby the local government unit is prompted to advance the lacking funds for the payment of the cost of the electricity and charged to other funds booked under the Trust Fund; 

a.	Require the concerned officials and employees in-charge of the billing and collection the electrical payments from the stallholders to reconcile the balances reflected in the List of Delinquent – Electric Bill and the Energy Deposit account booked under Trust Fund in order to establish the correct amount of collectible from the stallholders;

b.	Set-up a receivable account for the amount collectible from the stallholders and liability account recognizing the amount erroneously charged to other funds booked under Trust Fund; and

c.	Enforce the collection of the cost of electricity consumed by the delinquent stallholders.

